# Cursor Commands Format

## Required Structure
1. **Title**: `# Command Name` (single line, title case)
2. **Overview**: `## Overview` (1-2 sentences describing purpose/context)
3. **Steps**: `## Steps` (numbered list `1.`, `2.`, etc. with bold sub-headers `**Title**:` followed by comma-separated actions)
4. **Checklist**: `## Checklist` (checkbox items `- [ ] Description` covering all critical steps)

## Format Rules
- **Title**: Single `#` heading, title case, matches filename (kebab-case)
- **Overview**: Brief context, when/why to use, no bullet points
- **Steps**: Numbered (`1.`, `2.`), bold sub-headers (`**Name**:`), comma-separated actions in description
- **Checklist**: Checkboxes (`- [ ]`) mirroring Steps, one per critical action/verification

## Examples
```markdown
# Command Name

## Overview
Brief 1-2 sentence description of what this command does and when to use it.

## Steps
1. **Step Title**: Action one, action two, action three
2. **Another Step**: Action four, action five

## Checklist
- [ ] Action one completed
- [ ] Action two verified
```
